From 0d758327116615b7eb65f355d5180841b293e0e0 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Clayton Craft <clayton@craftyguy.net>
Date: Fri, 5 Jun 2026 14:07:41 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] A64-LTS: limit max freq

This works around an issue where my a64-lts board will unexpectedly
and abruptly reset if it performs concurrent read-modify-write memory
operations across 4 cores at these 'fast' speeds. Limiting the frequency
seems to effectively work around this issue, but this is obviously
papering over a bigger issue with the memory controller timing or ???

I used stress-ng to show that resets only happened when using --vm 4
(or greater), and with --vm-method flip. Using a write-only or read-only
method did not trigger the reset. So it's some combination of the memory
activity and operating higher frequency supported by the SOC.
---
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/allwinner/sun50i-a64-pine64-lts.dts | 5 +++++
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/allwinner/sun50i-a64-pine64-lts.dts b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/allwinner/sun50i-a64-pine64-lts.dts
index a67286eb5c53f..7a55f9dd55ee0 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/allwinner/sun50i-a64-pine64-lts.dts
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/allwinner/sun50i-a64-pine64-lts.dts
@@ -116,3 +116,8 @@ &mmc1 {
 	max-frequency = <25000000>;
 	status = "okay";
 };
+
+&cpu0_opp_table {
+    /delete-node/ opp-1152000000;
+    /delete-node/ opp-1104000000;
+};
-- 
2.54.0

